Week in Feedback=E2=80=A6
-------------------

On Simone Bellotti=E2=80=99s anticipated Bally exit: =E2=80=9CAgree that
Bellotti leaving Bally is bittersweet. Being Swiss, I was rooting for the b=
rand. (Not that Bally is truly Swiss. Like most brands headquartered in the=
 Ticino area, it employs almost exclusively lower-wage employees from nearb=
y Italy, and the design team probably spends the better part of its time in=
 a Milan-based showroom.) That being said, there are simply no resources le=
ft to build something. The brand is in pure cost-cutting mode. They are fir=
ing people left and
right. They closed the brilliant Fondazione Bally, which was headed by Vitt=
oria Matarrese and headquartered in a beautiful villa on the shores of Lake=
 Lugano. The brand has been switching owners seemingly every five minutes f=
or the past 10 years or so, which obviously prevented any strategic retooli=
ng. So they just kept spending as usual, while trying out things more or le=
ss at random. I'm sure Bellotti=E2=80=94which is right=E2=80=94was more an =
accident than anything.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A brand
consultant

=C2=A0

On the LVMH constituency at the inauguration: =E2=80=9CI tried hard not to =
message you regarding the Arnaults, but=E2=80=A6: Engaging with a governmen=
t is one thing, but attending the inauguration, vigorously clapping, and gi=
ving continuous standing ovations is another.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A strategic=
 advisor type=C2=A0

=C2=A0

On the Oscar de la Renta inauguration takeover: =E2=80=9CDon=E2=80=99t you =
just love having an excuse to call Alex Bolen? Love that guy.=E2=80=9D =E2=
=80=94A writer

=C2=A0

On my coverage of inauguration fashion, and Trump: =E2=80=9CI love you! And=
 I cannot with Trump Regime fashion reports. I beg you not to make this par=
t of your beat. Don=E2=80=99t you feel icky being right there with
Bezos and Zuck and everyone bending the knee to those people? Usha looks go=
rgeous! But her husband talks shit about women! Okay, it=E2=80=99s their bi=
g day and night. But for the most part, can you please leave routine report=
ing on their fashion to lesser mortals? You are the Dean! Let someone else =
do that dirty work. Fashion is where I come to hide from those people. You =
may have to follow the money, but you don=E2=80=99t have to kiss its ass.=
=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94Ruth Ann
Harnisch

=C2=A0

On our lack of e-commerce recs geared toward men: =E2=80=9CMen get the shop=
pies, too ;-).=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A lawyer [Ed. note: We hear you!]

=C2=A0

On Sarah=E2=80=99s Vuori analysis: =E2=80=9CLove the Vuori piece! Went to v=
isit family in San Diego over the holidays and got into a big discussion ov=
er whether this can make it and
how their store felt bland. It=E2=80=99s located right next to Lululemon so=
 we did both back-to-back and stood outside comparing. Family isn=E2=80=99t=
 in the industry and they didn=E2=80=99t get my skepticism or critiques, bu=
t=E2=80=A6 all valid points! All that said, I type as I=E2=80=99m wearing t=
heir pants now.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A brand marketer

=E2=80=8A

And finally=E2=80=A6 Did you know that Aritzia is not only knocking off The=
 Row (a
given), but also knocking off The Row=E2=80=99s lookbook ( https://www.ther=
ow.com/collections/spring-2024?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281=
