-wage employees from nearby Italy, and the design team probably spends the =
better part of its time in a Milan-based showroom.) That being said, there =
are simply no resources left to build something. The brand is in pure cost-=
cutting mode. They are firing people left and
right. They closed the brilliant Fondazione Bally, which was headed by <str=
ong>Vittoria Matarrese</strong> and headquartered in a beautiful villa on t=
he shores of Lake Lugano. The brand has been switching owners seemingly eve=
ry five minutes for the past 10 years or so, which obviously prevented any =
